            </h2>

            <p>State machines are the underlying components of many digital
                systems, providing the ability for such a system to react
                appropriately depending on inputs and past events. Sensor
                processing systems and controllers are typical examples. In
                this lab, a state machine will be developed as a controller
                of two trains on shared track segments. With two trains
                sharing a common track layout and activating sensors
                asynchronously. Care must be taken to account for all
                possibilities to successfully avoid collisions. The project
                will focus on enhancing understanding of VHDL, state
                machines, and particularly state machine design.</p>


